sights.name: Gamle Stavanger
sights.quote: Preserved 18th- & 19th-century white wooden cottages are the cornerstone of this historic district.

sights.name: Norwegian Canning Museum
sights.quote: Exhibits, equipment demos & films on the regional canning industry in a former factory complex.

sights.name: Stavanger Cathedral
sights.quote: Elegant medieval cathedral, Norway's oldest, with Gothic & Romanesque accents & vivid stained glass.

sights.name: Stavanger City Museum
sights.quote: Museum built in 1893 offering exhibits on local cultural & natural history, plus displays for kids.

sights.name: Stavanger Maritime Museum
sights.quote: Small dockside museum featuring ship models & artifacts related to Stavanger's maritime history.

sights.name: Norwegian Petroleum Museum
sights.quote: Petroleum museum by the port based in a stand-out landmark building built from different rocks.

sights.name: Breidablikk museum
sights.quote: Elegant 1881 manor featuring historic furnishings & antiques, plus English-style landscaped grounds.

sights.name: Stavanger Art Museum
sights.quote: Lakeside, sophisticated museum offering Norwegian & international artworks dating back to the 1800s.

sights.name: Jernaldergården
sights.quote: Replica of an Iron Age farmstead, with costumed docents, demonstrations & hands-on kids' activities.

sights.name: Sverd i fjell
sights.quote: Fjord-side monument to the 872 Battle of Hafrsfjord, with 3 10m-tall swords, made in 1983.

sights.name: Arkeologisk museum i Stavanger
sights.quote: Regionally focused archaeological & natural history exhibits dating to prehistoric times.

html_attributions: Arkeologisk museum, Universitetet i Stavanger. Museum of Archaeology, University of Stavanger

sights.name: LEDAAL
sights.quote: Grand, listed 1800s residence with Baroque gardens housing antique furniture & historic art.

sights.name: Norwegian Children's Museum
sights.quote: Institution with cultural & historical exhibits, plus a children's museum with hands-on displays.

sights.name: St Svithun's Church, Stavanger
sights.quote: Glass details flood this modern Catholic church with light during its regular services.
